Imagery Description: (a) Female head with white flesh, (b) r.f. female head
Additional Notes: In PAdd (p. 16) this vase was placed in the Group ofNaples 1778, but the use of white for the face of the head on the obverse, and the stylistic connection between the r.f. head on the reverse and that on no. 550 above suggest it is better placed here.
Artist: The Painter of Naples 2585 and his circle
